They had all that mess and containers filling the parking lot there.   I remember being so damned freaked out; because that is when I first learned about all this FEMA Camp stuff.   Then I was even more horrified when people were investigating this as far back as 2005 after Hurricane Katrina. After about 4 months, the metal boxes all finally disappeared... but that ominous memory still lingers.   Really spooky if you ask me.   So, that thank you very, very much for sharing this. Gosh darn it... why do I have to be poor?   I want my own damned basement bunker full of food!
